"If we can develop these cell and gene therapy treatments for patients suffering from absolutely devastating disorders, it can really change the lives of thousands and thousands of patients around the globe."

Our CEO Bill Anderson recently sat down with four scientists to learn more about the novel ways they are pursuing our mission, #HealthForAll, #HungerForNone. We’re calling the series “Science is Boss” – and we’ll be sharing the highlights of their conversations here over the coming weeks.

In episode one: Ruth Shah, a trained cell and molecular biologist, delves into the potential of cell and gene therapies to fundamentally change the way diseases like Parkinson’s are treated.

🌿✨ Discover Your Health Superpower! ✨🌱
 
When you think of healthcare, do you only picture doctors and hospitals? What if we told you that you have a health superpower right at home? It's called self-care. 🦸‍♂️🦸‍♀️ According to the World Health Organization @who, self-care is about taking proactive steps to prevent disease, maintain health, and manage illness.
 
Let's prioritize self-care not just for the personal benefits highlighted in the video, but also for the positive impact it has on society. What's good for you is good for everyone.
 
#HealthForAll #HungerForNone #SelfCare

The job of modern agriculture has always required farmers to be flexible and adaptable. But climate change is making the lives of farmers even more difficult: They are asked to grow more food for more people with fewer inputs and restore more of their local ecosystems at the same time. Check out how innovation from Bayer can help corn growers increase resilience and combat food insecurity around the world in the @WSJ article linked in our bio.

This is Jose. He is on a mission to help support farmers in Honduras. 

Many smallholder farmers find themselves lacking the services or support they need nearby. And yet, these same farmers are the backbone of their local communities’ food security, and they are important at global scale, too: they produce 1/3 of all food worldwide. There is enormous pressure to produce a fruitful harvest and support themselves and their family. 

Jose knows firsthand the struggles farmers are facing. But now he is in a position to share knowledge and best practices and provide services at a local level. He witnesses the huge positive impact this type of initiative has on smallholder farmers in his region of Honduras.

At Bayer, we want to live up to our role and responsibility as an impact generator. And we are redesigning the company to focus on what’s essential for our mission: #HealthForAll #HungerForNone. Thank you, Jose – and thank you to all the farmers around the world who are playing an important role in making this happen.

Did you know that over 100 billion bananas are eaten each year? They��re not just a favorite fruit: around 400 million people rely on them for their food security.

But banana plantations are under serious threat from Tropical Race 4 (TR4), a devastating fungus that can wipe out banana crops. Once it strikes, it’s nearly impossible to stop.

Together with our partners, we’re committed to creating a sustainable future for banana growers because for us, #HealthForAll, #HungerForNone starts in one place: the FIELDS! 🌱💚

#TeamBayer #RegenerativeAgriculture

Over the past four weeks, more than 30 athletes from Team Bayer gave their all in Paris. And the results were remarkable: 2x Gold, 2x Silver, 2x Bronze, and 5x 4th place finishes, along with numerous personal bests and strong performances.

🥇 Markus Rehm (Long Jump T64) and Taliso Engel (100m Breaststroke SB13)
🥈 Nele Moos (Long Jump T38) and Johannes Floors (400m T62)
🥉 Maurice Wetekam (100m Breaststroke SB9), and the first German Paralympic medal) and Irmgard Bensusan (200m T64), who is competing in her last Paralympics.
 
Team Bayer truly shined. We are inspired by the ambition, determination, and team spirit of all our athletes. As a sports sponsor for over 120 years, we are proud to witness our athletes chase their dreams. Huge congratulations to all athletes and coaches!

Stop using ChatGPT until you’ve done THIS:
Before you type another prompt, tell it:

✔️ Who your target audience is
✔️ What kind of result you want (sales, content, engagement, etc.)
✔️ What your brand vibe is (fun, professional, bold, soft, etc.)
✔️ What your content plan or pillars are (so it speaks your language)

I PROMISE—it will give you way better answers when it knows the full picture.

I used to get frustrated with generic results... until I started prompting like a boss.
Now ChatGPT feels like my personal content coach.

“There was a game he [Guardiola] put Zinchenko false-nine. Champions League, PSG at home. Crazy. The day before, he didn’t even put Zinchenko there in training, he put me at striker. Then the other day, Zinchenko even joked with me, ‘That day I felt bad for you’…

Two hours before the game, there’s a team-talk, the team eats, rests and goes. He gave the team, I didn’t even eat. I went crying, I called my mother, ‘I want to leave’. I’m going home, because he put him on and not me. He put a left-back there. I went crazy.

Within five minutes, Mbappé made it 1-0 PSG. Pep subbed me on, I gave an assist and scored, we turned it around 2-1. In the following game, I thought I was going to play. I didn’t.

There was a lot of that with Guardiola, it’s not easy. That’s when I decided, I didn’t want to stay anymore. I decided to leave.” 👀

Animal em situação de rua não é detalhe. É sinal de que precisamos agir com responsabilidade, humanidade e políticas públicas eficazes. Em Teresópolis, demos o primeiro passo com o Programa de Manejo Populacional de Cães e Gatos: castração, microchipagem e conscientização. Mais que números, esse programa é respeito à vida. Não é sobre fazer mais do mesmo é sobre fazer o certo. Com constância, seriedade e compromisso. E sigo pronta para levar esse modelo a outros municípios. A causa animal não pode esperar. 🧡

No Dia do Trabalho, estive em Três Rios e presenciei algo que nunca me canso de admirar: a força silenciosa de quem tem fé.
Ver tantos rostos jovens reunidos me lembrou que o trabalho vai muito além do sustento, ele nos dá sentido, direção, esperança.
Participar da reabertura da @fm92algonovo, ao lado dos meus pais, amigos e de tantas pessoas queridas, foi mais do que especial. Porque dar voz também é dar vez. E cada vez que nos reunimos em fé e comunhão, ajudamos a construir um futuro mais justo. 🧡

Um projeto necessário, sensível e profundamente humano.

Parabenizo o deputado Carlos Minc pela autoria do PL 3565-A/2017, que assegura às mulheres o direito de exercerem sua maternidade com dignidade, especialmente em contextos de vulnerabilidade.

Como mãe, apoio com o coração e com a responsabilidade de quem acredita que políticas públicas devem proteger vínculos, e não rompê-los.

Hoje, tive a honra de presidir uma sessão plenária na Assembleia Legislativa do Estado do Rio de Janeiro (Alerj). As palavras não conseguem expressar plenamente o turbilhão de emoções que vivi neste momento único. Foi uma experiência profundamente gratificante e uma honra imensa, simbolizando um avanço significativo na participação feminina em espaços de decisão. Neste Mês das Mulheres, este marco ressalta a importância de ocuparmos lugares de relevância em todas as esferas da sociedade. Minha gratidão ao presidente Bacellar por nos proporcionar esta oportunidade. Que este momento inspire outras mulheres a seguirem seus caminhos com determinação e coragem. 🧡
meu coração todinho 🩵
minha vida todinha 🫶🏼

Hoje recebi na Alerj a querida Majú de Araújo, a primeira modelo brasileira internacional com síndrome de Down, um símbolo de beleza, representatividade e força.

Ao lado da mãe, Adriana, e da irmã Larissa, que está sempre nos bastidores registrando, apoiando e caminhando junto, Majú representa uma família que luta unida por inclusão, visibilidade e protagonismo para pessoas com deficiência.

Entrei com o pedido da Medalha Tiradentes para reconhecer essa trajetória que inspira o Brasil. Que esse gesto ecoe para além das redes e fortaleça políticas públicas que acolham, respeitem e deem voz a quem por muito tempo foi silenciado.

É por ela e por todas as pessoas com deficiência que seguimos lutando por inclusão de verdade, mostrando que a luta se constrói em conjunto, com afeto e propósito.
Encerrando mais uma semana de votação no plenário da Alerj. ♥️

Teresópolis me recebeu com abraços, histórias e muitos rabinhos abanando. Estar com quem ama, protege e defende os animais é gratificante e tem muita gente boa fazendo o certo, mesmo sem aplauso. Cuidar dos animais é, sim, cuidar da cidade. E isso eu quero levar comigo por onde for. 🧡🐾
um pouquinho do nosso carnaval em família 🩵⚓️

If you see us parked out front, something good is growing inside. 🔥

Grower Stories, Episode 21

In this episode of our Grower Stories series, we head to Missouri for an inside look at Delphi Management, a 10,000 sq. ft. hybrid, positive-pressure greenhouse facility. Join us as we talk with David Risley, Director of Cultivation, about how they're pushing the limits of year-round growing—even in Missouri's unpredictable climate.

Delphi retrofitted their facility to combat extreme weather conditions with a BioTherm Plantcentric® System, a cutting-edge climate solution that helps maintain consistent growing temperatures, no matter what’s happening outside. They’ve also implemented a dissolved oxygen system to boost root health and improve plant performance.

With BioTherm technologies in place, Delphi Management is equipped to grow high-quality crops year-round—efficiently and reliably.
We can’t wait to see you at @greentechrai!
Still kickin’ since 1981 — this header’s been keeping the bench heat flowing for over 40 years. Talk about old-school reliability.

BioTherm makes hot water heating easy! ⁠
⁠
This shows our team manufacturing 2 different boiler room systems, one is using copper, the other traditional welded steel tubing. The copper "boiler loop" is going to integrate 3 boilers together (2 now, 1 future), and the steel one will connect 4- 400,000 BTUH high-efficiency boilers. The copper system is bound for North Carolina, and the Steel system is going to Florida— both are going to blueberry growers! 
⁠
By doing the hard parts of BioTherm systems with pre-assembly, we make it easy for growers to benefit from world-class, high-efficiency heating.

@Jethrobovingdon was tasked with charting the progress of driver aids through three generations of #BMW M3s. First was the timeless E46, the earliest model with any form of dynamic stability control (DSC). Then came the E92, which featured M Dynamic Mode (MDM), a new intermediary setting for the DSC. Finally, we have the current G80 M3 in basic rear-drive, manual-gearbox configuration. The six-speed ’box and two driven wheels link the new car directly to the E46, but its electronics are of an entirely different order. The G80 supplements MDM with a traction-control system you can tailor to your needs and the subtle differences of the road or track you’re negotiating.

The #AstonMartin Vantage Roadster shares all of its major mechanical components with the Coupe version. Power comes from an AMG twin-turbo 4.0-liter V-8, but this has been substantially reworked to increase peak output to 656 hp and 590 lb-ft.

On Aston’s numbers, the Roadster is only 132 lbs more than the Coupe. Aston claims a 3.5-second 0-60-mph time, just a tenth behind the coupe, with both cars having an identical claimed 202-mph top speed. The company says the Roadster’s power-operated fabric hood is the quickest on the market, able to open or close in just 6.8 seconds and operate at speeds of up to 31 mph.

All three of these answers are actually correct!
A will takes effect after death, detailing asset distribution, while a living will guides decisions during incapacitation.

A living will focuses on healthcare preferences, unlike a will, which doesn’t cover medical decisions.

In a will, you appoint an executor for estate management; a living will allows you to express your wishes regarding life-sustaining treatment.

Both documents serve crucial, yet distinct roles in ensuring your wishes are honored. Enlightening, right? Let’s embrace these tools to secure our futures comprehensively. 📜 💡

¡Las tres respuestas son correctas!
Un testamento entra en vigor después del fallecimiento y detalla la distribución de los bienes, mientras que un testamento vital guía las decisiones durante la incapacidad.

Un testamento vital se centra en las preferencias de atención médica, a diferencia de un testamento, que no abarca las decisiones médicas.

En un testamento, usted nombra a un albacea para la administración del patrimonio; un testamento vital le permite expresar sus deseos con respecto al tratamiento para el soporte vital.

Ambos documentos cumplen funciones cruciales, aunque distintas, para garantizar que sus deseos se cumplan. Esclarecedor, ¿verdad? Aprovechemos estas herramientas para asegurar nuestro futuro de forma integral. 📜 💡

Many people think happiness lies in the next place, the next achievement, the next relationship — as if peace is waiting just around the corner, one life change away. 

But no matter where you go, there you are. 

You bring your thoughts, your emotions, your patterns, and your restlessness with you.

If you can’t find contentment within, no location will provide it. 

If you can’t appreciate being alive right here and now, you likely won’t appreciate it in some other time or place. 

If your mind is chaotic, even paradise will feel like a prison. 

Real peace is not found by running away or reaching some new destination — it’s found by turning inward, by learning to be fully present with yourself here and now, and by being in touch with the wonder of life in each moment. 

When you can be at ease within your own being, and fully present with life as it is in each moment, the whole world becomes your sanctuary 🙏💚

Creamy Lemon Parsley Pasta
Serves 4
About $2.50 per person. 

Ingredients
1/2 yellow onion, sliced 
2 cloves garlic, whole
1 Tbsp olive oil
1/2 lemon, juiced
15 oz cooked chick peas, drained
1 tsp rosemary
2 Tbsp grated vegan parmesan
2 vegan chicken bullion cubes 
A few sprigs of fresh parsley, torn
1 lb pasta of choice
Water
Salt snd pepper 

Directions:
Cook pasta in a large pot according to pavkage directions (reserve 1/2 cup pasta water before draining)

In a frying pan on medium heat: 

Add oil, onion, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes. 

Add beans and enough water to barely cover the mixture. 

Add bulllion cubes and stir. 

Add the fresh lemon juice, stir, and cover the pan. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes then pour into a blender. Add a handful of the fresh parsley and blend until smooth. Then return the blended bean mixture to the frying pan.

Add parmesan, pasta water, stir, and then fold the pasta into the bean sauce to coat. 

Rip a few parsley leaves on top, add a touch more olive oil If you want and enjoy!  If you love the texture of mac and cheese, youll love this recipe.

On this day in 1965, the historic Selma to Montgomery March culminated as thousands of demonstrators arrived at the Alabama State Capitol, marking a pivotal moment in the fight for voting rights. ⁠
⁠
Led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., the marchers embarked on a five-day, 54-mile journey. Under federal protection, they covered about 12 miles a day and slept in fields and makeshift camps along U.S. Route 80, enduring physical exhaustion and threats to demand equal voting rights for African Americans.⁠
⁠
The march followed earlier attempts that were met with violent opposition, notably the events of "Bloody Sunday" on March 7, 1965, when peaceful protesters were brutally attacked at the Edmund Pettus Bridge. Despite these challenges, the marchers persevered, and their efforts contributed significantly to the passage of the Voting Rights Act of 1965, a landmark achievement in the Civil Rights Movement. ✊🏾 #BlackHistory⁠
⁠

• GRACE AND COURTESY WITH YOUR BIGS • 

Like 🫶 and comment MANNERS and I’ll send the link to your DMs 🔗 

As my two bigs are getting bigger, I’m finding a lot of new situations popping up where some explicit explanations/practise are helpful for them to understand more complex situations and contexts. Situations which require ‘manners’ or ‘courtesy’ in particular, for example manners around being served food that they don’t like, or introducing yourself to new friends, or not staring when they seem someone who looks different from themselves. 

This flipbook was recommended to me by a friend and it’s now become our dinnertime conversation starter. I flip through it if there’s anything in particular I’m feeling we need to cover, and it provokes great discussions without being directed at any particular child, meaning we cover these topics from a joint place of curiosity rather than from a place of critique. 

It gives a short, sharp, easy to understand explanations that make tricky topics easy to talk about and easy for kids to understand, and has been a really valuable tool to have in our home to help cover grace and courtesy with our young children!

• SCHEMAS OF PLAY • 

Like this reel ♥️ and comment SCHEMAS and I’ll send a link to your DM’s for you to receive a downloadable doc all about the schemas of play! 🔗
.
Schemas are a pattern of behaviour that you might notice in your child’s play - like lining objects up in a line, or dumping out tubs of toys - that repeats itself across many areas of play. Schemas are not developmental or ‘fixed’ - two children of different ages may be working within the same schema, and a particular schema may be observed for weeks, months or even years. The different play schemas are:
Orientation 
Positioning 
Scattering 
Enclosure 
Trajectory 
Enveloping 
Connecting 
Transporting 
Rotating 
Transforming 
.
My document gives a run down on each one and examples of the types of activities you can try if you observe these patterns of play in your child! 
.
.

People ask me what it’s like to homeschool four kids, and I don’t know how to explain that it’s really just living our lives alongside each other. It’s not something we slot into every day, it IS every day. It’s not one part of our life, it IS our life. It’s not a neat little box I can tick, it’s a beautiful mess of ideas and experiences, that we come out the other side of having grown and changed and learned things without being able to pinpoint the exact moment that any of it happened. 
There’s no set of steps, no secret recipe, except letting go of the idea that there’s anything else we ‘should’ be doing that’s more valuable. There’s nothing more valuable to me than building strong relationships with my kids, and to give them time to build strong relationships with themselves and each other 🩷 I hope they remember their childhood with nothing but love, just like I will.

PS. Hi 👋🏻 we’re back on the gram 😆 if you’ve been with us a while, thank you for still being here ☺️ and if you’ve never seen us before, I’m Emma! I was a primary school and early childhood teacher and now I’m a stay at home mum/homeschooling mum to my four girls. We live in Brisbane and love life 🫶🏻 I’m all about play and following my kids interests and natural development 🌱

• DIY CHRISTMAS SNOW GLOBES • 

Like ❤️ and Comment SNOWGLOBE (one word!) and I’ll dm you the links to the things we used 
. 
These are the easiest little DIY’s to do with your kids, and are a fun joint holiday project for 3 years + 🎄
.
They would also make cute Christmas gifts for friends or family! 
.
How to:
- Use hot glue to glue a figurine to the base/lid of the globe. Make sure your figurine isn’t too small/flat or you won’t be able to see it once the water is in the globe. You can use a plastic block to raise the figurine if needed, by gluing a plastic block/part (such as a bottle cap, mini container etc) to the base and then gluing the figurine on top. We used the clear containers left from the glitter we poured into the snow globes to raise the smaller figures so they could be seen! 
- Fill the globe with water (almost to the top, you need a small amount of space so it shakes up properly) 
- Tip glitter flakes/sparkles into the water, along with a small amount of glycerine (around 1-2 teaspoons, you can add more after if the glitter is falling too quickly, the glycerine slows down the glitter falling to give the ‘snow’ effect)
- Screw the lid on so that the figurine is immersed in the water. Tighten.
- Shake it up and watch the glitter fall like snow! You can add more glitter or glycerine as needed, until you are happy with the result ❄️ 
.
You can also hot glue the lid on at the end if you wish (I didn’t do this as I wanted to be able to remove the lid to add more glitter if needed)
.
.

So, what happened at Bayer in the first quarter of 2025? We've still got a lot of work to do. But we’re getting more focused, and we're holding our ground.
 
Curious what #TeamBayer is concentrated on going forward? Hear from our CEO Bill Anderson as he reflects on the last 90 days and gives an overview of what you need to know in 90 seconds ☝

🌟 What's the largest organ of our body? It's quiz time! And today's topic?  Skincare!
 
Test your knowledge together with our colleagues Tabea and Chris, and challenge your friends to see who reigns as champ!

Addressing the world’s greatest challenges requires more than investing in transformative technologies—it demands building societal acceptance. This begins with actively listening to people’s hopes and concerns about breakthrough science.

@leapsbybayer, our impact investment arm, collaborated with @bcg and market research by @IPSOS_UK to conduct one of the largest surveys on global public sentiment towards transformative technology. 

Over 13,000 participants from 13 countries were asked about their outlook. 72% of respondents express confidence in the direction of science and technology. 

At Bayer, these insights fuel our mission and support our drive to innovate responsibly and communicate meaningfully. Whether it’s advancing cell and gene therapies to tackle Parkinson’s disease or revolutionizing agriculture to help work towards food security, we remain committed to leading with science and building trust.

Find the link to the full report in our bio.

🚀  What excites or surprises you most from this study? Let’s keep the conversation going in the comments!

💔 Heart failure is a major global health challenge, impacting over 64 million people. 🫀 Despite advances in care, survival outcomes for those with heart failure can be as grim as those with some common cancers. This serious condition weakens the heart’s ability to pump blood, leading to symptoms like fatigue and shortness of breath, which can make daily life a struggle. 

Early recognition is key! Each heart failure event increases risks, so spotting the signs early can save lives. #TeamBayer’s goal is to reduce the impact of heart failure and empower patients to reclaim their lives. ✨

#HeartFailureAwareness

Nutrition is vital for human health and development. Yet globally one in three people survive on diets that lack the essential vitamins and minerals needed to grow properly and live healthy lives.

Our Nutrient Gap Initiative aims to impact 50 million people in underserved communities by 2030, focusing on expanding access to essential vitamins, minerals, and diverse nutritious foods. In 2023, we reached over 30 million people. 

And our portfolio of innovative products and solutions empowers farmers to bring high-quality, nutritious foods to the table. 

#HealthForAll #HungerForNone

💗 Women's health matters. That's why we're innovating across multiple areas to support women's unique healthcare needs. 

From heart health to vision care, supplemental breast cancer screening options to menopause solutions - we're here for women at every stage of life. 

Did you know? 

• Stroke affects more women than men 
• 2.2 billion people face vision challenges 
• 2.3 million new breast cancer cases yearly 
• 47 million women enter menopause each year 

We're committed to supporting women. Because you are more than a statistic and your health matters 💙

Every mom dreams of giving their baby the healthiest start possible, but the reality is that many factors can affect a child's health right from the beginning.🌍✨ In underserved communities, vitamin and mineral deficiencies are a serious issue, especially for women and children who are most at risk. Our Research Initiative for Self-Care Equity shows that infants born into lower socioeconomic situations are 60% more likely to suffer from anemia because their moms often lack access to proper nutrition.🤰🥗

That’s why we’re all in with our #NutrientGapInitiative! By 2030, we aim to ensure that 50 million people in underserved communities have access to essential vitamins and minerals every year. Our activities range from supporting smallholder farmers who grow fresh fruits and veggies to advancing vital micronutrient supplementation. 🌱❤️

Together, we can empower communities to thrive, nurture healthier families, and create brighter futures for all.

#HealthforAll #HungerForNone

‘Deep breaths, in and out’ is a familiar mantra that many use to get through tough moments during the day. But what happens when those deep breaths don’t come easily?

Allergic diseases like asthma, allergic rhinitis, and eczema affect 34% of people worldwide, hitting vulnerable populations the hardest due to air pollution and poor housing. 🌬️🏠

Through our Research Initiative for Self-Care Equity (RISE), we’re diving into the complexities of these conditions. These insights help us tackle health disparities and design self-care solutions for those who need it most. By advocating for policy changes and supporting access to resources, we can unite to help people enjoy life without the burden of allergies. 💚

Check out the link in bio to explore various socioeconomic factors affecting health.

#HealthForAll #HungerforNone #HealthEquity

Last week I had the honor and privilege of talking to 400+ incoming 1Ls at St. Thomas University Benjamin L. Crump College of Law’s first day of orientation. ⚖ 

The topic was “Mental Wellbeing, Happiness & Success in Law School and Beyond” and we talked about key practices for managing stress, anxiety, imposter syndrome and other common challenges so many law students and law face through their careers.

I strongly believe that in order to work together to improve the mental health of our profession, we need to talk candidly about these challenges and to provide impactful tools for a healthier, happier and more balanced career. 

A huge thank you to my alma mater for prioritizing this topic, starting from day one, and I appreciate you Josh Heath, Esq. for making it happen.

The journey through law school is undoubtedly a challenge, and maintaining a strong mental health is not always easy. 

In fact, according to The Path to Lawyer Well-Being (ABA, 2017), “Law students start law school with high life satisfaction and strong mental health measures. But within the first year of law school, they experience a significant increase in anxiety and depression. Research suggests that law students are among the most dissatisfied, demoralized, and depressed of any graduate student population.” 😱 

But, it doesn’t have to be this way. There are countless tools and resources out there, and sometimes it starts with conversation and vulnerability. We can rewrite the narrative and create a healthier profession. If you are a law school, bar association or law firm, and you would like collaborate on ways to improve our profession together, let’s chat.

 #lawschool #mentalwellbing #lawyers #mentalhealth

Dealing with another rent increase? Don’t panic! Try these simple tips to reclaim your power as a renter.💪⁠
⁠
1️⃣ Approach your landlord with a win-win proposal. Offer a longer lease term in exchange for a smaller increase, or highlight your stellar tenant history as leverage. It doesn't hurt to ask!⁠
⁠
2️⃣ Get a roommate (or two)! Splitting costs can significantly ease your financial burden. Plus, you could gain new friends in the process!⁠
⁠
3️⃣ Tap into local resources. Many cities offer rent assistance programs. Do your homework and don't hesitate to seek help - that's what these programs are for!⁠

4️⃣ Try PadSplit coliving! Our affordable shared homes can save you 40-50% compared to regular apartments. Enjoy a private, furnished room with one simple weekly payment that covers rent, utilities, Wi-Fi, and laundry access.⁠
⁠
5️⃣ Familiarize yourself with local rent control laws and tenant rights. Understanding the legal landscape can give you a powerful edge in negotiations.⁠
⁠
Remember, you have more options than you might think. Stay proactive, stay informed, and don't be afraid to think outside the box. Your perfect housing solution is out there!⁠

Healing isn’t always loud. Sometimes it’s quiet, a small step taken every day, a gentle decision to keep moving forward. And you’ve done that. You’ve survived what you thought would break you. Take a moment to celebrate your resilience. You’ve come so far, give yourself credit for the strength it took to get here.

This is a prayer for your heart, for all the parts of you that feel wounded, lost, or heavy. May you find the healing that you need. May the weight on your shoulders lessen, and may the pain be replaced with peace. You deserve joy, wholeness, and rest from the struggles. I hope you find your way to it soon. 🌻

2025 the year of soft growth, of intentional living. This is the year where you embrace the beauty in the small things, books that expand your mind, friends who nourish your spirit, and the space you make by letting go of anything that dulls your light. Let 2025 be the year you unapologetically choose joy, creativity, and the love you deserve.

There is no rulebook that says you need to follow the path everyone else is walking. Your journey is your own, and what you need right now may be vastly different from what the world expects of you. It’s okay to carve your own way, to pause, to create a route that serves your spirit. Being true to yourself is always more valuable than fitting into someone else’s mold. 🌻

Knowing where you stand in someone’s life isn't about accepting less; it’s about honoring yourself by seeing things as they are, not as you wish they could be. There is power in clarity. When you understand the role you play for others, you can guard your heart, find peace, and invest in those who truly show up for you. Love doesn’t have to hurt. Let it guide you towards those who care for you, just as much as you care for them.

Give your energy to those who truly see you. Don’t settle for one-sided connections. Protect your time, because it’s one of the most precious things you have, and it’s too valuable to be wasted. Drop a ❤️ if this resonates.

May 2025 be full of people who match your energy and make you feel valued. But remember, it’s okay to let go of anyone who can't see your worth, because walking away is also a form of love for yourself. Drop a ❤️ if this resonates.

Yes we signed a prenup. Mostly because of studies showing that couples that do tend to get divorced less not more.

When Jacob bought himself a $10,000 bike without asking me… I knew we were on a different page when it comes to spending 🥲

Money has always been a tension point in our relationship.
Not because we don’t love each other. because we love each other so much we ignored the money conversation for a long time hoping that it will sort itself out.

I’m a saver. He’s a spender.
I make more right now—but I still want him to buy the groceries.
But… when we first met, the roles were reversed!

So before we got married, We signed a prenup.

Here are the uncomfortable questions that saved us from resentment 

(Follow @aggie for more!)

	• How much can you spend—$500? $5,000? $50,000—without telling me?

	• Are we combining accounts or keeping some money separate?

 • What’s our financial safe number? (Not your dream number—your I can breathe again number.) $50k in savings? Or $5k?

	• What happens if one of us stops working for a baby, burnout, or a dream?

	• How do you really feel about a woman earning more? (Hint: most men hate it)

	• Are you still okay with paying for things if I’m making more?

	• What’s your actual debt situation? Credit score? Skeletons?

	• What does “rich” mean to you? (To me: freedom. To him: toys.) but also: is rich $1m, $10m or $100m?

	• Are you a saver or a spender—and does your nervous system feel safe with mine?

	• What do we do with bonus money, inheritance, or gifts?

	• Do you support your family financially—and is that non-negotiable?

	• Can we adjust our lifestyle when things shift? Or do we cling to what we “used to afford”?

	• Do you believe in budgeting—or is that my job forever?

	• Who tracks spending? Who pays for what when we travel?

	• How do you want to raise kids around money? Are we aligned on values?

	• Can we talk about money without shutting down or blaming?

	• And the big one: if one of us gets sick, are we ready to carry the weight—financially and emotionally?

This stuff isn’t unromantic. What’s unromantic is silence!!!

The baby is a … 🩷🩵 😍

We always imagined we would have a girl first but the moment Aggie got pregnant she was convinced it’s a boy. But then the extreme morning sickness came, the family / grandparents and friends voted girl so we were walking into this moment really not sure what to expect.…

Our reaction - 🫠🥲

Most wellness advice wasn’t made for women. In fact, following it might be the reason you’re not seeing results !!! For the last 5 years, I’ve been cross-referencing research to make sure the advice we follow actually applies to us, ladies.

Here are 5 trends that are bs 👇

❌ Trend #1: Intermittent Fasting every day!

Women’s bodies are more sensitive to energy deficits. Daily fasting can lower kisspeptin—a molecule that regulates GnRH → LH/FSH → ovulation.
Translation? You could suppress your cycle, slow your metabolism, and increase belly fat.

✅ Better: Fast in your follicular phase. How? More on that in my cycle syncing @bestie.app! 
📚 Harvard Med (2013)

❌ Trend #2: Ice Baths

Cold plunges are great for dopamine… but timing matters.
In menstruating women, constant cold exposure activates norepinephrine and cortisol → can lead to adrenal fatigue over time if you’re already stressed, under-eating, or over-training.

✅ Better: Cold exposure 1–2x/week in your follicular phase, not every day. In luteal? Prioritize heat therapy (saunas, baths, walking outside).
📚 Kregel et al., 2002:

❌ Trend #3: Replacing Meals with Green Juice

Uncooked cruciferous veggies like raw kale and broccoli contain goitrogens—that inhibit iodine uptake, which can reduce thyroid hormone production (extra fat storage!)

✅ Better: lightly cook your greens—this reduces goitrogens by up to 80%. (Also in my @bestie.app!!!)
📚 Rose et al., 1995 and Gunnars, 2013

❌ Trend #4: Low-Fat Everything

Your hormones are literally built from cholesterol.
Going too low-fat = your body can’t produce enough estrogen, progesterone, or cortisol and worsen PMS.

✅ Better: Eat fats from egg yolks, grass-fed butter, fatty fish, and olive oil. Especially critical in luteal phase.
📚 Wang et al., 2000:

❌ Trend #5: HIIT & running

Daily HIIT depletes progesterone, which worsens PMS, sleep, and even fat loss resistance. Plus it leads to type 2 muscle fiber burnout—these are your power, strength, and longevity fibers.

✅ Better: Lift heavy in your follicular and ovulatory phases. Walk, stretch, or do Pilates luteally. Train like a woman in my @bestie.app —not like a bootcamp bro.

📚 Tomiyama, 2012

I always get hate on this, because people think I don’t like pilates. 

I don’t hate Pilates. I actually do it. I love doing it.
We have sooo many pilates classes at @bestie.app and they are hard!
Just like I like walking, dancing, and swimming. 

But I don’t confuse those with what builds muscle, burns fat, and balances hormones.

Muscles are hard to build for us women because we don’t have as much testosterone as men, but they act like a sponge for insulin resistance which is at the root of your gut issues, low energy, belly fat, acne etc etc 

Most women don’t realize:
Pilates doesn’t apply enough resistance to trigger real muscle growth. It targets type 1 muscle fibers—great for endurance, posture, and rehab.

But the ones that shrink as we age? (We all age)

Those are type 2 muscle fibers—the ones responsible for your metabolism, insulin and body composition.

Only lifting weights activates those.

And why do we care?

Because muscle isn’t just for “looking toned.”

It literally acts like a metabolic sponge—soaking up glucose, regulating insulin, and stabilizing your blood sugar (which is what helps prevent fat storage and cravings).

Here’s what lifting with progressive overload actually does for women:
	• Increases insulin sensitivity so you can burn fat instead of store it
	• Lowers cortisol, especially when paired with rest days (unlike endless cardio)
	• Boosts growth hormone and testosterone (yes, women need that too)
	• Creates muscle reserve so you bounce back faster after stress, sickness, or pregnancy
	• Supports thyroid and adrenal function
	• Improves estrogen metabolism and helps prevent dominance

No, Pilates doesn’t do that.

If you’re constantly bloated, tired, or holding fat in your belly or thighs despite “doing everything right,” this is why.

You’re not building muscle. You’re not lifting heavy enough. You’re not progressing.

And if Pilates makes you feel good right now? Amazing—do it.
But please don’t confuse it with what your body needs for true transformation.

Peanut meeting our son - I don’t think my heart can handle it 😭 - how did your dog take their arrival of the baby?

Also - at home OBGYN visits > everything else.
What else did it miss? Whats the propaganda you’re NOT falling for?

Pregnancy is the most intense metabolic event the human body can handle.

You burn more energy than climbing any Everest —
2.2x your basal metabolic rate for 270 days straight.
The max human limit?
2.5x!!!

You’re basically living in ultra-marathon mode while growing a whole human.

And while you’re at it?
You grow a brand-new organ from scratch—the placenta.
It has more blood vessels than your lungs.
You rewire your brain, double your blood volume, and run two immune systems at once.
(And somehow still get sh*t done.)

And yet…
after all that,
the first thing people say is:
“Wow, you got big!”
Or:
“So when are you planning to bounce back?”

You just built lungs, kidneys, a heart—
and we’re still reducing women to their waistlines.
Even in our most powerful biological state,
we get judged on appearance! Or stretch marks or face acne.

Wouldn’t you be tired if you were creating life from scratch
while holding down a job and pretending everything’s fine?

Here’s the truth:
Most women go into pregnancy depleted, under-muscled, and overwhelmed.
No one teaches us to train for this.
But athletes do.

They fuel.
They prep.
They recover with intention.
And that’s exactly how we should be treating pregnancy too.

Because whether you’re pregnant, postpartum, or just navigating hormones like a boss—

You are an ultra-endurance athlete in disguise.

You deserve deep nourishment,
actual rest,
and way more respect than a “are you sure it’s not twins?”

I had no idea what’s about to happen - and that my entire life’s mission is helping women understand the power of their period and their cycle! and that I will using tracking cycle to lose weight to work out and eat!

Back then? I was annoyed!!! (white pants had something to do with it). 😂

I liked not having it.
No cramps, no mess, no tampons.
All I cared about was fixing my bald patches and clearing my skin.

But what I didn’t know back then?

A healthy period is one of the most powerful indicators of health!!!

If it’s regular (but not too long, too heavy, too short, or too light), it means your body finally feels safe again.

It’s your hormones saying: “We’re good now. Let’s thrive.”

Getting my period back was the start of my healing.
of course, my hair and skin followed.
So did my fertility! 

Here’s what helped:
	1.	Healing my leaky gut. Everything shifted once I got my digestion under control — from inflammation to skin.
	2.	Eating fats I was scared of for years. Ghee, egg yolks, coconut cream — the ones your hormones actually love.
	3.	Living in sync with my cycle. I finally stopped pushing myself to eat and train the same every day like a machine.
	4.	Getting support. I worked with Dr. Melissa — who’s now the Head of Science at my supplement company and teaches monthly classes inside the Bestie app. How wild is that?

So yeah, I didn’t celebrate it at first.
But now?
That first “ugh” moment turned out to be the first sign I was finally healing.

It how is your relationships with your period?

I’m a wellness girlie and not ashamed to admit…

🩷 I still slip into the masculine side of wellness.
Even though I talk so much about healing from a soft, feminine energy — I still catch myself tracking everything, measuring progress, trying to “fix” my body with discipline.
I know better. I teach women this.
But sometimes the perfectionism sneaks in.
And instead of nurturing my body, I try to outsmart it.

🩷 I think wellness has gotten way too serious.
Somewhere along the way we made health… feel like another job. And honestly?
I’m here for more freedom, more energy, more joy and more laughter!
Not to live in fear of the wrong oil touching my lips.
There’s a playful, wild, messy side of health that we’ve forgotten — and I’m on a mission to bring it back. And some people in the space are so an*l they bore me to death 😂
Because you can optimize your mitochondria and vibe in the kitchen.
Take supplements and eat cake with your best friend.

🩷 I find it overwhelming to keep up with all the biohacking research.
One week coffee’s a neurotoxin, the next it’s longevity juice.
Protein is queen… until it’s not.
Gut health matters, but also your trauma, your cycle phase, your mouth tape, your attachment style — and now I need to fix my fascia??
It’s a lot.
And if I feel that way — as someone who lives and breathes this world — I can only imagine how it feels for women just starting.

🩷 Not everyone in my life has “drunk the Kool-Aid.”
Some of my closest people still think this wellness thing is just expensive pee or that I’m doing too much.
But I’ve learned that not everyone’s ready at the same time.
And that doesn’t make them wrong, or me better.

🩷 I believe mindset overrides biology — and I forget that too.
I’ve built an entire brand around the science of wellness… but truthfully?
The most powerful shifts I’ve experienced came when I changed how I thought.
Not what I ate. Not when I fasted. Not even what I took.
I try to communicate that with my @bestie.app, but I’m not sure if I’m failing.

MY BIRTH STORY: It all started about 1 week prior to Rio being born with me having small contractions every now and then during a few nights. It felt like a small period cramp but nothing that bothered me too much. They came very unregular and could vanish for a night or so before coming back. 

On Friday evening ( 21st of February) I went to my friend Magdas place and had a movie night, when I felt a change in the contractions, but still not to the point that I felt that something was happening. That night I woke up with more contractions but not in a way that I felt was to take action on. I took a hot shower and went back to sleep. 

On the 22 of February I woke up with contractions being gone again and went on with my day. Later that evening I had scheduled to swing by my other apartment since I had sold it and was supposed to give them the keys on Monday. Right before Jesper came home from work I started feeling contractions again and now a bit more frequent. We made dinner and ate it in front of the TV when I started to feel the contractions get closer to each other. But in my mind I was like ”nah, this is not it. They are so manageable and it’s my body playing tricks on me. And yeah, I still need to swing by my apartment to get the last bags of clothes from the attic”. Said and done - I jumped into a cab and went to get the bags, carrying big bags of clothes up and down the attic ( yes, I’m a very stubborn person). Once back home again I started to feel even more contractions and closer and closer to eachother,  but not too painful and I didn’t want to go in to the hopsital only to be sent back home if I wasn’t open enough.

Anurag slams 100 in Dattu Phadkar Under-15 meet

In the Dattu Phadkar Under-15 Tournament Pre-Quarterfinal matches on Monday, St Johns Public School and Cathedral Mission High School bagged victories to enter the quarterfinals. 

In the first match, Anurag Chakraborty smashed a brilliant 100 as St Johns Public School beat Sri Aurobindo Vidyamandir by 166 runs.  St Johns Public School scored 249/9 in 44 overs. Sri Aurobindo Vidyamandir were 83/3 in 24.5 overs when rain stopped play. Eventually, St Johns Public School were declared winners by virtue of higher run-rate. Jishnu Ghish bagged 4 wickets. 

In the second match, Cathedral Mission High School won by spin of coin against Siliguri Boys High School.

The Bengal Pro T20 League Season 2 is all set to roll on. On May 19, the Men’s Draft was held at a glitzy and star-studded ceremony. We visit the key moments from the mega draft through our lens.

#CAB

First Div Championship: Gearing up for the final

The countdown begins. After a nail-biting league and knockout stage, the top two teams, Bhawanipore Club and East Bengal Club will face-off in all-important First Division Championship final on June 1 at the iconic Eden Gardens. 

The summit clash will be a five-day Day-Night match which will be played in pink ball.

Prior to the crucial match, both the teams Bhawanipore Club and East Bengal Club underwent a practice session at the Indoor facility of the Eden Gardens on Wednesday.

The players from both the teams got to opportunity to familiarize themselves with the pink ball. 

The players got a feel of the pink ball’s grip, bounce, and swing. Both the team’s bowlers and batsmen strategized their approach.

#CAB

It’s Sobisco Smashers Malda vs Murshidabad Kings in Bengal Pro T20 League Season 2 opener

The Bengal Pro T20 League Season 2 will commence on June 11 at the iconic Eden Gardens with Sobisco Smashers Malda taking on Murshidabad Kings in the opening match. 

Following the opening day’s match, the men’s league will see double headers being played till June 24. The league matches will conclude on 25th June.

The semifinals will be a double-header affair at the Eden Gardens to be played on June 26th from 1pm and 7pm onwards.

The grand final will be held at the Eden Gardens on June 28 from 7 pm onwards.

#CAB

Alok slams 101 for Suburban Club in Second Div Championship final

Alok Sharma smashed a brilliant 101 off 99 balls as Suburban Club managed to post 229/5 in 42 overs at stumps on a rain-interrupted Day 1 against Behala Friends Union Club in the Second Division Championship Final at the Eden Gardens on Sunday.

Besides Alok, Pratik Dutta also impressed with a fine 54. 

For Behala Friends Union Club, Asparsh Singh was the pick of the bowlers bagging 2 for 57.

#CAB

Rain-hit Day 2 in Second Div Championship final at Eden Gardens 

Rain had the final say on Day 2 as only 7 overs could be bowled in the Second Division Championship Final between  Suburban Club and Behala Friends Union Club at the Eden Gardens on Monday.

At stumps on Day 2, Suburban Club were 284/5 in 49 overs with the match being reduced to 58-overs-a-side.

Dipak Prasad (45 not out) and Gautam Verma (27 not out) were still at the crease. 

Earlier on Day 1, Alok Sharma smashed a superb 101 as Suburban Club reached 229/5 in 42 overs at stumps.

#CAB

Suburban Club crowned champions of Second Div Championship

Suburban Club outclassed Behala Friends Union Club by 97 runs in the summit clash at the Eden Gardens on Tuesday to emerge champions of Second Division Championship.

Batting first, Suburban Club scored 284/5 in 49 overs. Alok Sharma (101), Pratik Dutta (54), Dipak Prasad (45 not out) and Gautam Verma (27 not out) were the star performers with the bat. 

For Behala Friends Union Club, Asparsh Singh was the pick of the bowlers bagging 2 wickets.

Chasing a revised target of 233 in 40 overs on the third and final day, Behala Friends Union Club managed to score only 135/8 in 40 overs.

For Suburban Club, Monomit Mitra (4-64), Abhishant (2-9) and Md Ashif (2-18) were superb with the ball.

#CAB

Bengal Pro T20 League Season 2 to begin on June 11

After the grand success of the inaugural edition, the Bengal Pro T20 League Season 2 will commence on June 11 with the men’s competition at the iconic Eden Gardens.

While the men’s league will begin on June 11, the women’s competition will start the next day on June 12 at the JU, Second Campus Ground, Salt Lake.

In the opening match of the men’s league, the joint winners from last season Sobisco Smashers Malda and Murshidabad Kings will face each other at the Eden Gardens from 8pm onwards. 

Following the opening day’s match, the men’s league will see double headers being played till June 24. The league matches will conclude on 25th June.

The semifinals will be a double-header affair at the Eden Gardens to be played on June 26th from 1pm and 7pm onwards.

The grand final will be held at the Eden Gardens on June 28 from 7 pm onwards.

In the women’s league, the opening match on June 12 will be a double-header clash with last season’s finalist Murshidabad Kueens taking on Harbour Diamonds in the morning match from 9am onwards while defending champions Lux Shyam Kolkata Tigers will face Servotec Siliguri Strikers in the afternoon match from 1:30pm onwards. 

The women’s league will see double header matches being played till June 25.

The semifinals will also be a double header affair at the JU, Salt Lake campus on June 27th from 9am and 1:30pm onwards. 

The final will be played at the Eden Gardens on June 28 from 1:30pm onwards.

#CAB

Sougata Roy (3-19, 27), Priyanshu Sarkar (2-16) impress in Dattu Phadkar Under-15 meet

In the Dattu Phadkar Under-15 Tournament Quarterfinal matches on Wednesday, Purba Barasat Adarsha Vidyapith and St Johns Public School bagged wins to enter the semifinals. 

In the first match, Purba Barasat Adarsha Vidyapith beat Cathedral Mission High School by 5 wickets. Cathedral Mission High School were bowled out for 105 in 39.4 overs. Sougata Roy (3-19) and Priyanshu Sarkar (2-16) impressed with the ball. In reply, Purba Barasat Adarsha Vidyapith scored 106/5 in 30.3 overs. Rahul Mondal (28) and Sougata (27) were the pick of the batters. Aryadeep Mandal bagged 2 wickets.

In the second rain-hit match, St Johns Public School won by spin of coin against Chanchal Siddeswari Institution.

#CAB

Argha (5-18), Souvik (4-12) impress in Dattu Phadkar Under-15 meet

In the Dattu Phadkar Under-15 Tournament Pre-Quarterfinal matches on Tuesday, Purba Barasat Adarsha Vidyapith and Chanchal Siddeswari Institute bagged victories to enter the quarterfinals. 

In the first match, Purba Barasat Adarsha Vidyapith beat Jiaganj Raja Bijoy Singh Vidyamandir by 7 wickets. Batting first, Jiaganj Raja Bijoy Singh Vidyamandir were bundled out for 73 in 24.4 overs. Argha Das was superb with the ball bagging 5 for 18. In reply, Purba Barasat Adarsha Vidyapith scored 74/3 in 20.5 overs. Sougata Roy top-scored with unbeaten 19.

In the second match, Chanchal Siddeswari Institute beat JL Vidyabhaban Rampurhat by 2 wickets. JL Vidyabhaban Rampurhat were bundled out for 61 in 22 overs. Souvik Saha (4-12) and Iftikhar Ahamed (3-17) were superb with the ball. In reply, Chanchal Siddeswari Institute scored 62/8 in 17.4 overs. Md Jubayed top-scored with 16 runs. Ekbal Sk and Srijon Saha bagged 3 wickets each.

Great time yesterday at @fitzgeraldsnightclub- gave a reading & was in conversation with @heshlamont about my new book, Just Beyond the Light, for the @chihumanities Spring Festival. Thank you to everyone who came out, especially the infamous Frank Pollard of “Terror & Hubris in the House of Frank Pollard.”

Then we cruised over to see my friend & @pigface_official bandmate, Martin Atkins AKA @flowersfightforsunshine at his #museumofpostpunkandindustrialmusic- this place keeps on getting better and better & wilder and wilder every time I come back. Lots of historic relics here, including a couple of Steve Albini’s 2-inch tape machines- it’s so cool for me to look at these machines & think about albums I have loved since highschool being recorded on them (RIP Albini, you cantankerous punk rock genius, you!) If you’re ever in Chicago, be sure to go check out the museum. 

Chicago rules!

Lourdes (@lourdes_music) y Keith Barrera (@keithbarrera_) se presentarán juntas en la décima edición del festival de electrónica más grande de Colombia: el BAUM (@Baumfestival). Aunque la primera haya crecido en Ibagué y la segunda en Bucaramanga, se han convertido desde la pandemia en dos de las máximas representantes de una nueva camada de mujeres DJs en Bogotá.

Sin embargo, cada una representa una visión diferente de los sonidos más estridentes: la cabeza del Studio 401 (@_studio401) es más de la corriente histórica, ortodoxa, identificada con el hard techno y el schranz; mientras que Keith es de la nueva escuela, a menudo llamada neorave. Detrás de su B2B hay un intento previo fallido, transformaciones personales y una escena en evolución a pesar de su división.

Design-Driven. Nature-Connected. One-of-One Over the Potomac. 

Another Exclusive HEIDER Private Offering | 5124 Wissioming Road, Bethesda, MD📍

Presented by @danielmheider & @karaksheehan. 
____

Overlooking the Potomac in scenic Glen Echo, 5124 Wissioming Road is a modernist masterpiece by Robert M. Gurney, FAIA. His signature style; interconnected forms in Corten steel, wood, and glass—harmonizes with the natural topography to deliver bold architecture and panoramic river views. A striking addition by Christopher Tucker and Square One Development further elevates the design.

A dramatic approach features whimsical landscaping, a covered carport, heated 4-car garage, and a bridge leading to the grand entrance. Inside, slender steel windows in a Mondrian layout frame river views, while terrazzo floors and mahogany paneling set a tone of minimalist luxury. The chef’s kitchen, with sleek Varenna by Poliform cabinetry and Miele appliances, connects seamlessly to the dining area and screened-in porch with fireplace. Upstairs, a glass bridge leads to the private primary suite, featuring floor-to-ceiling views, balcony, dual offices, and a limestone-clad bath with soaking tub, sauna, and dressing room. The lower level impresses with a 1,000-bottle wine cellar, fitness center, guest suite, and a two-story library with cantilevered bridge.

Outdoors, a 66-foot lap pool, built-in grill, and fireplace make for effortless entertaining. Ten-zone HVAC, Lutron lighting, Sonos sound, a Generac generator, and smart home systems complete this architectural triumph. 
_____

Price Available Upon Request.

Experience the Pinnacle of Phillips Park Living at Tuesday’s Broker’s Event | 4414 W Street NW, Washington, DC📍

Open May 27th | 12:00 PM - 2:00 PM | Offered for $5,250,000. 
_____

Nestled in the rolling hills of Phillips Park, an exclusive enclave of just 46 custom residences tucked along DC’s esteemed Foxhall corridor, 4414 W Street NW is a bespoke estate that sets a new standard in luxury living. Designed through an extraordinary collaboration between Sandy Spring Builders, GTM Architects, and renowned interior designer Marlene Alexander, the home seamlessly blends timeless elegance with modern sophistication.

Graciously scaled formal living and dining rooms flank the central hall, featuring a coffered feature wall, Niermann Weeks and Murano glass chandeliers, and exquisite millwork. The chef’s kitchen is outfitted with a Viking six-burner range, KitchenAid refrigeration, waterfall granite countertops, and a custom limestone backsplash, opening into a sunlit breakfast room and expansive informal family wing. Here, cathedral ceilings, a fieldstone fireplace, and a dual-zone layout create perfect flow for gatherings, while four sets of French doors open to a flagstone terrace with panoramic views of the Washington Monument. Upstairs, the primary suite is a private retreat with 16’ ceilings, a limestone fireplace, motorized shades, a boutique-inspired dressing room, and a spa bath with heated floors, marble vanities, a steam shower, and a jetted tub. Additional features include two upper-level ensuite bedrooms, a mirrored fitness room, guest quarters, a full mudroom, a three-car garage with epoxy flooring and custom workbench, plus an elevator and sophisticated systems: Lutron lighting, Sonos sound, Ring + Crimpco security, fire suppression, copper plumbing, and central vac.

Finished with architectural landscape lighting and full irrigation, this residence is an extraordinary offering in one of the Capital’s most coveted residential communities.

Follow @danielmheider through Washington’s Finest Residential Offering | 3030 Chain Bridge Road NW📍

Offered for $19,995,000. 
____

3030 Chain Bridge Road NW represents a faithful reinterpretation of 18th-century English precedents encased in a modern package. A collaboration between Jones Boer Architects, @banksdevelopment, and @arentzla united three of the city’s most significant long-standing industry names in meticulously handcrafting a home whose proportions, materials, and workmanship harken back to a bygone era.

Prominently perched on the site of the renowned Cafritz Mansion, the rare, nearly 39,000 square-foot lot enables a gracious crescent drive and separate motor court, affording a resplendent approach to the grand estate. Unobstructed forward vistas overlook verdant parkland and soaring mature trees. Painstaking studies of distinguished local mansions and the works of John Russell Pope were scrutinized for their scale, proportions, and details.

In the rear, a wide loggia bridges the relationship between indoor and outdoor spaces. A harmonious blend of minimalist landscaping and extensive limestone hardscaping creates a natural oasis, completely removed from the urban environment beyond. 

A four-car garage, industrial-grade support systems, including geothermal HVAC, 800-amp electrical service, a full house generator, Savant automation with audio-visual capabilities, and a comprehensive Lutron lighting suite, add layers of modern livability. As one of the finest estates in the Capital Region, 3030 Chain Bridge Road NW will undoubtedly be immortalized among Washington’s most distinguished homes.
____

12,911 Sqft | 8 Beds | 13 Baths 

Visit 3030ChainBridge.com to learn more.

Offered for: $9,495,000.
____

Nestled amidst towering trees and rolling lawns, The Owl’s Nest is a historically significant estate in Forest Hills that embodies the perfect union of classic elegance and modern design. Originally crafted by celebrated Washington architect Appleton P. Clark in the late 19th century, this landmark home has been meticulously restored, expanded, and modernized under the visionary architect George Myers and the renowned Gibson Builders. Every detail has been thoughtfully reimagined, preserving its historical integrity while meeting the demands of contemporary luxury living.

Spanning 10,100 square feet, the home’s expanded footprint doubles its original size to seamlessly blend formal and informal spaces. The original wing celebrates its heritage with meticulously restored millwork, stately fireplaces, and a breathtaking library featuring a barrel-vaulted ceiling, wood paneling, and abundant natural light. The newer wing introduces a relaxed, contemporary ambiance, centered around a state-of-the-art chef’s kitchen equipped with custom inset cabinetry, thick-edge marble countertops, and top-of-the-line SubZero and Wolf appliances. Adjacent gathering spaces, including a semi-circular breakfast nook and a cozy family room with a coffered ceiling, exude warmth and sophistication.

Situated on 1.56 elevated acres, the estate’s grounds are as breathtaking as the home itself. Rolling hills shaded by mature trees provide a tranquil backdrop, while the expansive rear patio—complete with a rectangular lap pool and privacy walls—is perfect for al fresco dining and entertaining. The Owl’s Nest is more than a home; it is a rare and irreplaceable piece of Washington’s history, masterfully redefined for today’s most discerning buyers.

I met Jean Biermans randomly out on the road in Cape Town a few years ago, he is very well known Dutch rider and has multiple wins at the 36ONE MTB Challenge.

36ONE MTB Challenge is a 361 Km endurance race. Jean not only has won but also set the course record of  14 hours 03 minutes 57 seconds.

But for me the impressive part of this story is how Jean had to fight back after a terrible accident.

in 1991 when Jean, was hit by a bus and dragged for more than 15 meters – leaving the lower part of his left leg torn off, resulting in a very close call to amputate his leg.
It took the doctors three operations in which they eventually managed to repair his leg. This was no easy task because every muscle and tendon around his knee was ripped off completely and the skin and most of the muscles were gone. The surgeons took skin from his upper legs on both sides to reconstruct new skin over his lower leg.

It took two years of practice and physical therapy before he was able to walk without crutches. Some of us can relate to this story of tragedy and courage but all us can be inspired by people like Jean that never say die.

In the last words Jean wrote me today in a mail : Life can suck... but if you really want... success is around the corner.

Jean happy cycling mate, we look forward to see what you get up to next.

You can follow Jean here on Instagram @jeanbiermans74

Jeg hjelper deg med alt du trenger for å komme i form og få resultatene du ønsker🌟. Korte og effektive økter, raske og sunne oppskrifter og mye mye mer! 👊😊

Jeg er så glad for å dele en spennende nyhet med dere her fra vakre Rhodos! Jeg har nettopp ferdigstilt min aller første e-bok – “Komplett E-bok til å Bli Sunn og Sterk - Trening, Kosthold og Motivasjon!” 📖💪
Denne e-boken er laget for å hjelpe deg med å oppnå dine helse- og treningsmål. Den inneholder alt fra hvordan finne motivasjon, sette realistiske mål og lage en handlingsplan, til kostholdstips, effektive treningsrutiner, og hvordan unngå skader.

E-boken lanseres i begynnelsen av august, og den er helt gratis! Så følg med her på profilen for oppdateringer og lanseringsdato! 🌟

Innhold:
- Motivasjon: Finn din indre drivkraft og sett realistiske mål
- Handlingsplan: Sammensatt SMART-mål
- Kosthold: Enkel og næringsrik mat for maksimal ytelse
- Trening: Forslag til en treningsuke
- Gjennomføring: Hvordan holde seg til treningsplanen og oppnå resultater
- Skader: Forebygging og behandling av vanlige treningsskader
- Neste steg: Fortsett din reise

Det blir så gøy å dele denne reisen med dere! 🥳✨
Hold dere oppdatert, og vær klar til å bli Sunn og Sterk! 💚

Ydmyk og takknemlig for så gode tilbakemeldinger fra gjengen i Sunn & Sterk❤️! Det er en drøm å følge utviklingen i gruppa, og få ha det så gøy med trening🏃🏼‍♀️‍➡️🏋🏼‍♀️

Om du også vil bli med, sjekk ut linken i bio. Det er ny oppstart 12. august🔥

Jeg elsker å kjenne følelsen av en skikkelig treningsøkt, men motivasjonen kommer og går, og noen dager virker det blytungt bare å skulle få på seg treningstøyet🫠 Har du det også sånn av og til?🫵

Her skal du få høre mitt aller beste tips for å bygge treningsmotivasjon🏃🏼‍♀️🙌🏼☀️

Ta deg en treningsøkt!!

Ja, du leste riktig, men hør meg ut. Den absolutt beste måten å bygge motivasjon for trening er faktisk å trene, og det aller vanskeligste med det er å komme i gang!😅

Ta på deg treningstøyet kjapt, og start de første 10 minuttene av økta, uten å tenke så mye. Kjenner du at det var nok, kan du gå inn igjen, men jeg er ganske sikker på at du vil føle deg mer motivert av faktisk å ha trent!👏

Ikke still for høye krav til deg selv, men få på deg joggeskoene, og ha fokus på treningsglede og ganske snart vil motivasjonen komme sigende av seg selv🤩

Vil du lese hele min artikkel om motivasjon, eller ha korte og effektive økter, spesielt designet med fokus på treningsglede og resultater? Da er Sunn & Sterk noe for deg! Der finner du det og mye mye mer!! Ny oppstart er 9.september💪 meld deg på i dag: link bio

Har du planer om å løpe fort, og lurer på hvordan du skal forberede deg best mulig? Hent inspirasjon fra min oppvarmingsrutine til løpeintervaller eller løpekonkurranser🏃🏼‍♀️‍➡️ En kjapp, trygg og god måte for å få varmet opp kroppen, og for å aktivere de eksplosive muskelfibrene. Husk, kjør ankelhopp til slutt, da det er lurt å være god og varm før denne øvelsen! 

Vil du ha flere treningstips, sjekk ut Sunn & Sterk, hvor det er  ny oppstart 12. august! Der har jeg bl.a en komplett pakke for å være best mulig forberedt til @oslomaraton  og @kkmila.no Lykke til, jeg heier på deg 👊

1️⃣Lett jogg 10 minutter
2️⃣Tripping (rull fra tåball til hæl)
3️⃣Høye kneløft
4️⃣Spark bak 
5️⃣Tå touch
6️⃣ Stigningsløp
7️⃣ Lette Ankel hopp / eksplosve ankelhopp (kan gjøres på startstreken)

Gjennomfør alle øvelser 3 x 15 sekunder med 15 sekunder pause🏃🏼‍♀️‍➡️👊

Lyst på 5 kjappe mageøvelser til neste økt? 
Kjør disse 45sek med 15 sek pause 3 ganger.

I 2022 la jeg skiene på hyllen, fordi jeg ønsket å stifte familie, men har fortsatt å trene fordi det gir meg så mye glede❤️! Både i NM og på tester virker det fortsatt som om jeg har noe å bidra med i skisporet, og lysten til å ha startnummeret på brystet er like sterk. Etter to begivenhetsrike år på sidelinjen, har jeg igjen fått muligheten til å bli en del av langrennsatsingen til Norges Skiforbund, og ønsker å gi drømmen om VM på hjemmebane en sjanse🌟! Jeg er spent på å se hva som er mulig å få til, og håper jeg får ta del i folkefesten som VM i Trondheim kommer til å bli. Vi sees i løypa 👊😍

🗒️ Directions for Use:⁠

An athlete sometimes never knows when they’re truly retired…and all good things come to an end right!? NOPE, I’ll be competing once again for USA in Tokyo at 2025 Deaflympics this winter.

Swimming has always been a huge role in my life but my motivation for swimming stems from within me to always want to advocate for the deaf community and finding ways to inspire and motivate others whether it’s on Reality TV, sports, or everyday life. I want to make sure I always continue doing something that’s going to make a change or even a small step in the right direction not just for myself but for everyone else who goes through similar struggles in everyday challenges in life.

I currently hold 22 total Deaflympic medals and the most in History has been set at 32 Total medals across 5 Games, and this will be my 4th Games where I plan to accomplish it and raise the bar to an even more difficult feat for the world to witness that we can accomplish anything we set our minds to as long as we want it, work for it, and go chase it, IT WILL HAPPEN 🏊🏼

📚Story time on the origins of Nutrafol:

It started with three people—each on their own emotional and physical journey with hair thinning.

💬 In medical school, Dr. Sophia Kogan faced so much stress, her hair began to thin. The irony? She was learning how to care for others, but had no tools to care for herself. That moment sparked her interest in holistic, whole-body healing.
💬 Giorgos Tsetis, a model in his 20s, found himself quietly panicking as he lost his hair. Prescription meds came with side effects he never expected—and a feeling of helplessness he couldn’t ignore.
💬 And after a major health scare, Roland Peralta turned to biohacking to support his whole-body health—including the hair thinning he never saw coming.

Each of their individual stories merged into one mission: to create a better way forward for those struggling with hair thinning. They needed answers for their our struggles so they could support the people all over who were struggling too. So that’s what they did.

🌱They identified 6 key root causes of hair thinning and created formulas targeting them with science-backed, bioavailable ingredients. Then they went further, launching clinical trials to prove the results were real. Because they weren’t just solving for hair thinning. They were building something bigger: a way to help people grow into the most confident version of themselves through hair health and whole-body wellness. And that’s where the story began. But it’s only just getting started.

WHAT IS VIETNAMESE ÁO DÀI? 👗

Literally translated to “long shirt,” áo dài is considered the national garment of Vietnam. It is a form of traditional Vietnamese formalwear — consisting of a long tunic (split at the sides) worn over a pair of wide-legged silk trousers 👖

Áo dài was born in the 18th century by the Nguyễn lords in Phú Xuân — but the modern + more form-fitting version that we know now was popularized in the 1930s, heavily influenced by French haute couture. While typically depicted on women, áo dài can be worn by all genders!

We love wearing our áo dài to temple to celebrate the New Year — but they can generally be worn to all sorts of special occasions, like weddings or holiday celebrations 🏮 Happy Year of the Dragon 🐲

“We see far because we stand on the shoulders of giants.” 🏔️

This International Women’s Day, we celebrate the true OG whose spirit vibrates throughout Omsom - our Bà Nội (or paternal grandma) 🙏🏽

The quintessential Vietnamese matriarch, Bích-Anh single-handedly raised 6 children in Saigon with only a third-grade education. In her day, Vietnamese women didn’t have much opportunity / economic mobility, especially if not born into affluent families. Ông Nội, or our grandfather, was a general in the Vietnam War, so she was left to take care of the family during some truly harrowing war times.

Bà Nội is the strongest woman we know — and while we have a tricky relationship with this narrative of the relentlessly “strong Vietnamese woman,” we continue to be inspired by her discipline + dedication. Bà Nội is the reason we (and Omsom) exist in the world today 🧡

Some fun facts about Bà Nội:
☸️ She now lives in southern California, where she remains committed to her Buddhist faith + regularly donates to her local temples.
🪡 She is a really talented sewist (which @kimoftheinternet takes after).
💭 Papa Pham considers her to be very progressive, because of how hands off she was with raising us 😋

Hope y’all are able to take stock today of whose shoulders you stand on 🙏🏽 We love you, Bà Nội!

💡 Tax Season Legal Tip

 Did you know that most personal injury settlements are not taxable?

If you received compensation for physical injuries or illness, the IRS typically does not treat that money as income. That means your settlement—meant to cover pain, suffering, and recovery—is not something you owe taxes on.

✅ No taxes on your justice
✅ No taxes on your healing

You are being made WHOLE again, not profiting.

It’s one of the few areas where the law and fairness align. As always, check with your legal or tax advisor—but know your rights this tax season.

Since sharing that we will be closing at the end of June, we’ve heard from so many of you. We’re grateful for the care and encouragement.

We’re here through next month, and we’re not slowing down. We’ll be running programs and hosting events for New Mainers right up until our final day.

On June 3, we’re offering a free workshop for immigrant women thinking about starting a business. If you’ve been wondering where to begin, this is a great first step.

Tap the link in our bio to register. 

More events to come soon!

Happening tomorrow! 

We’re teaming up with the Bayside Neighborhood Association for a Samosa Social on our 1st floor starting at 4 PM.

Bring a snack to share if you’d like, or just stop by to enjoy good food, great conversation, and the chance to connect with neighbors. Everyone’s welcome.

Something very exciting is happening at IWC this week, and we hope you'll be able to join us!

We’re thrilled to welcome the Voices of Renaissance choir from Boston Renaissance Charter Public School. For 25 years, these talented students have shared songs of hope and unity, performing everywhere from the White House to the March on Washington anniversary.

They’ll be joining us on Thursday, May 15 from 3 to 4 pm for a free concert on our first floor. 

We’d love for you to stop by and be part of it.

IWC will be closed tomorrow, April 21, in honor of Patriots' Day.

We look forward to welcoming you back on Tuesday!

If you’ve been meaning to build a website for your business but don’t know where to begin, this workshop is for you.

We’ll cover the basics, from choosing a name for your site to simple tools like Squarespace and WordPress. You’ll leave with a clearer sense of how to get your business online quickly, easily, and without needing a background in tech.

This session is part of our Business Basics Bootcamp series, offered through the Business Hub with support from the @mainetechnologyinstitute. It will be led by Nick Rimsa, a Portland-based designer who has helped launch over 50 products and worked with small businesses across Maine.

Join us Thursday, May 1 from 3:00 to 5:00 PM at 24 Preble Street, 3rd floor. Interpretation available.

Register through the link in our bio!

We’ll be closed most of Memorial Day (Monday, May 26), but from 3 to 4 PM, our doors will be open for something truly special.

Artist Daniel Minter, co-founder of @indigoartsalliance, and artist Rosalba Breazeale will be at IWC to lead a free community bead-making workshop. Participants will hand-form clay beads that will become part of In the Life of Trees, Daniel’s upcoming public sculpture for this year’s Deconstructing the Boundaries symposium.

Each bead will carry a personal hope or intention and be added to a larger work grounded in unity, reflection, and care for the future.

We hope you can join us!

Some hard news to share.

After more than seven years of serving New Mainers at 24 Preble Street, the Immigrant Welcome Center will close its physical location at the end of June. This decision was not made lightly. Despite every effort to keep the Center open, the loss of key federal funding created a gap we couldn’t close.

Walk-in services will end on June 30, but some programming will continue this summer, including Soccer Saturday and offsite English classes. We are working closely with community partners to explore what is possible beyond this moment and to support clients through the transition.

We are proud of what this space has meant to so many people, and especially proud of the immigrant communities, staff, and volunteers who made IWC what it was.

We have turned off comments on this post so our team can get some much-needed rest over the holiday weekend. If you have questions or thoughts to share, please email info@welcomeimmigrant.org or board@welcomeimmigrant.org.

This is a loss not just for us, but for the many people who relied on this space. We hope you will continue supporting the communities we have been honored to welcome.

This service is free!

If you're interested in updating your resume or if you're an employer or recruiter who wants to connect with us about workforce support, email Belinda at belinda@welcomeimmigrant.org.

This Monday, May 19, our friends and long-time supporters @androscoggin.bank will be at IWC to teach a free financial literacy workshop.

They’ll cover the basics of personal finance and help you better understand how banking works in the U.S. Whether you’re new to the system or just want a refresher on things like budgeting, saving, and credit, this is a great opportunity to build your knowledge.

Join us from 3 to 5 p.m. at IWC (24 Preble Street).

We hope you can join us!

The Saturday night before Easter, I came down with the stomach flu. Now, mind you…I haven’t been sick in over 12 years. That’s what living your Best Life can do for you. 😊 But this flu was a BEAST!

I’ll spare you the gory details, but I will share a few revelations that surfaced amidst the fever.

✅If you don’t slow down, life will slow you down. As much as I encourage others to be balanced, sometimes I don’t follow my advice. I work long hours and rarely take time off. "Physician heal thyself!" I know. However, when your mind, body, and soul need rest…that is what they’ll get! Don’t challenge them…you will lose!

✅Learn to be still. As soon as I started to feel a little better, I set up camp on my sofa and decided to wax poetic on social media. What followed was a minor relapse. My body shut down! My vision blurred, I couldn’t concentrate, and I slept on the sofa well into nightfall. Growing up…idol time was equal to being lazy, and that’s a myth I still battle with, but downtime…the "white space"…can be a time of great revelation, which leads me to the next part.

✅The work will wait. For an entire week, I didn’t post or make videos or coach. I didn’t cook, catch up with friends, or anything else. I sat on my deck and listened to birds. I lay on my sofa in silence and fell in love with my home again, and took long naps with the dog. When I returned to my desk this morning, guess what was waiting for me? Stuff! In all my 30+ years in corporate, I’ve never seen “the work” disappear. So, be sure to incorporate more downtime in your schedule.
